review_blob: Not my favorite cheap-o.  Never really understood the why its called Red Dog, it doesnt really have a red color to it like a Killians.

For wannabes who are trying to look "street".  Smells bad and tastes worse.  Why would anyone buy this in a can?  If you are going to drink malt liquor you have to have it in a 40, wrapped in a brown bag, and you should be sitting on the front stoop while sippin on it.

I remember when I was 19 I bought a case of High Life and stuck it in the trunk of my car for a roadtrip that weekend.  Mom found the case and confiscated it, I ended up having to buy Keystone to replace it (tight budget).  That was disappointing and so was the taste of the Stone.  "Bottled Beer Taste in a Can" my ass.  Ugh.  Buy it only to boil brats.
That hornet on the cap is the feeling youll have in your head if you drink more than a couple of these hand grenades.  A classic punchline beer that you should only buy for the humor effect.

Drank this after playing "ball" (softball) with some friends up in Calgary.  Always had drank Golden before that and I found Canadian to be slightly better.  Basically the High Life of the Great White North.
Hard to find in the Midwest, Id take this over Blue any day.  Id liken it to the Michelob of Canada.
Decent.  I liked it better ten years ago.  You could do alot worse than the Rock.  Ive always liked the painted label...
Decent cheap-o.  I used to love the old motion signs youd see at the VFW when your grandparents took you to the fish fry.  Ya hey dere.

"Buschhhhhhhhhh!!!"  I will say they used to have some good commercials.  Remember the one where the girl opens the bottle on her belt buckle and the beer comes spurting out on her stomach?  That said, this is a poor mans beer and is best suited for making bread or boiling brats.  Ill drink it if theres nothing else available.

This beer was made to be consumed in a tallboy can.the metallic taste actually helps.  All I can say about "Old Swil" is that they sell 10 ounce cups for a buck at Sycamore Speedway.  Nothing like bringing back a tray of 20 to your group while watching your buddy crash his 78 Cutlass in turn 3.

One of those beers that is nostalgic for some people.  Picked up a 30 pack over the summer more for the humor than the flavor.  "PBR me A.S.A.P."!!!  Not a bad beer for a hot Saturday afternoon while mowing the lawn.

Picked up a growler for the Bears game.  Needless to say the Demolition Ale was easier to take than the demolition of the Monsters of the Midway.  Strong, bitter hop flavor, dont really get the alcohol kick until you reach the bottom third of the glass.  More please...

This is one of those "when in Rome" beers.  When in a reggae bar, it just feels right to have a Red Stripe in hand.  Decent flavor, gotta love the painted bottle.  Better than the usual Bud/Miller product.

Another decent cheap Wisconsin brew.  If you cant find Huber in the back of the liquor store, go with the Rhiney.  The brown bottles are great for storing your homebrew.  A great beer to bring to a party to shake things up for the poor saps who live and breathe Bud.

One of my favorite cheap beers.  Gotta love the cardboard case with the brown returnables (which are great for bottling your homebrews, eh Dirk?).  Id take this over any Bud or Miller product hands down.
Id say this is practically a barleywine.  Pretty strong stuff.  Can be a bit much for the novice beer drinker...not for the faint of liver.  A good after dinner beer.
Great in bottles, even better on tap.  This is an old reliable Pale Ale that tastes especially good on a hot summer day.

This may have been every Illinois and Wisconsin kids first beer.  Definitely better on tap than in the can or bottle, although not by much.  Not the same as when it was brewed up in La Crosse.  If you want to taste the true "Old" Old Style as my guys call it, try a La Crosse Lager.  The employees of the former Old Style brewery in La Crosse bought it and reopened as City Brewing a few years back, and use the same methods.

Good beer to boil your brats in for the tailgate.

One of my favorite Chicago area brews.  Some people are turned off by the strong banana flavor but I dig it.  A good weiss for people who dont like weiss beers...not as strong of a wheat taste as others youll find.

This is what I like to call a good "work" beer.  Something to wet the whistle on a Saturday afternoon while painting the house, changing the oil, or cutting the grass.  Buy it for quantity, not quality.  Ive had worse.

This ale is a great bottle to take to a party and start conversations.  People who only drink Lite will ask "what is that?" and anyone with an open mind will be begging to try a swig.  Just the fact that its called "The End of the World" puts it high on my list.  Great citrusy flavor but not too malty.
Not the worst Oktoberfestbier you can drink, but not the best either.  Get a couple of 5 liter mini-kegs and wish you were in Munchen instead.
If you can find it on tap, its even better than in the bottle.  Im a big fan of La Fin Du Monde but Im starting to dig this one even more.  A great beer after a steak dinner.
